{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.39",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 39,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 39",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 39 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:1",
      "text": "Knowest thou the time when the wild goats of the rock bring forth? or canst thou mark when the hinds do calve?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:2",
      "text": "Canst thou number the months that they fulfil? or knowest thou the time when they bring forth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:3",
      "text": "They bow themselves, they bring forth their young ones, they cast out their sorrows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:4",
      "text": "Their young ones are in good liking, they grow up with corn; they go forth, and return not unto them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:5",
      "text": "Who hath sent out the wild ass free? or who hath loosed the bands of the wild ass?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:6",
      "text": "Whose house I have made the wilderness, and the barren land his dwellings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:7",
      "text": "He scorneth the multitude of the city, neither regardeth he the crying of the driver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:8",
      "text": "The range of the mountains is his pasture, and he searcheth after every green thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:9",
      "text": "Will the unicorn be willing to serve thee, or abide by thy crib?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:10",
      "text": "Canst thou bind the unicorn with his band in the furrow? or will he harrow the valleys after thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:11",
      "text": "Wilt thou trust him, because his strength is great? or wilt thou leave thy labour to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:12",
      "text": "Wilt thou believe him, that he will bring home thy seed, and gather it into thy barn?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:13",
      "text": "Gavest thou the goodly wings unto the peacocks? or wings and feathers unto the ostrich?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:14",
      "text": "Which leaveth her eggs in the earth, and warmeth them in dust,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:15",
      "text": "And forgetteth that the foot may crush them, or that the wild beast may break them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:16",
      "text": "She is hardened against her young ones, as though they were not hers: her labour is in vain without fear;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:17",
      "text": "Because God hath deprived her of wisdom, neither hath he imparted to her understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:18",
      "text": "What time she lifteth up herself on high, she scorneth the horse and his rider.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:19",
      "text": "Hast thou given the horse strength? hast thou clothed his neck with thunder?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:20",
      "text": "Canst thou make him afraid as a grasshopper? the glory of his nostrils is terrible.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:21",
      "text": "He paweth in the valley, and rejoiceth in his strength: he goeth on to meet the armed men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:22",
      "text": "He mocketh at fear, and is not affrighted; neither turneth he back from the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:23",
      "text": "The quiver rattleth against him, the glittering spear and the shield.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:24",
      "text": "He swalloweth the ground with fierceness and rage: neither believeth he that it is the sound of the trumpet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:25",
      "text": "He saith among the trumpets, Ha, ha; and he smelleth the battle afar off, the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:26",
      "text": "Doth the hawk fly by thy wisdom, and stretch her wings toward the south?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:27",
      "text": "Doth the eagle mount up at thy command, and make her nest on high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:28",
      "text": "She dwelleth and abideth on the rock, upon the crag of the rock, and the strong place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:29",
      "text": "From thence she seeketh the prey, and her eyes behold afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.39.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:30",
      "text": "Her young ones also suck up blood: and where the slain are, there is she.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
